-- Marano May Get $475 Million for Broadgate Sale, Times Reports
-- B y   K a t i e   L i n s e l l
-- 2012-02-19T09:50:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-19/marano-may-get-475-million-for-broadgate-sale-times-reports.html
Gemini Commercial Investments Ltd.’s
Peter Marano may get 300 million pounds ($475 million) selling
the Broadgate West commercial office complex near  London ’s
Liverpool Street Station to the developer Hines, the Sunday
Times reported, without saying where it got the information.  The move comes after a deal to sell half the site to
 Canada ’s Brookfield fell through last year, the newspaper said.
Marano is being advised by CBRE, according to the Sunday Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
